{"lemma":"مَشُوبٍ","slug":"مَشُوبٍ","root":"ش.#.ب","root_slug":"ش-_-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-_-ب","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n23263"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%B4%D9%8F%D9%88%D8%A8%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n23263","headword_ar":"مَشُوبٌ","root":"$wb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$iybN","text_ar":"مَشِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the latter from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iyb","text_ar":"شِيب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[“ it was mixed ”],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mixed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb.) A poet says, (namely, Suleyk Ibn-Es-Sulakeh EsSaadee, TA,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"wamaA='u quduwrK fiY AlqiSaAEi ma$iybu"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And the water of cooking-pots, in the wooden bowls,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mixed"},{"kind":"text","text":"with seeds for seasoning and with sauces. (S.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfatoHapu Alma$uwbapu biAlkasorapi","text_ar":"الفَتْحَةُ المَشُوبَةُ بِالكَسْرَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The fet-hah that is mingled with kesreh;"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the fethah that precedes the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_imaAlap","text_ar":"اـِمَالَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAbidN","text_ar":"عَابِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaArifN","text_ar":"عَارِفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[when they are pronounced “ 'ébidun ” and “ 'érifun ”]; for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AmAlp","text_ar":"امالة"},{"kind":"text","text":"consists in inclining [the sound of] fet-hah towards [that of] kesreh; whereby [the sound of] the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"that follows it is inclined, and is not a pure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for like as [the sound of] the fet-hah is mingled [with that of kesreh], so is [the sound of] the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[mingled with that of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (L, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}